\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. T. alpestre} Jacq.,{\i  Enum. Stirp. Vindob.} 116, 260 (1762) ({\i T. kerneri} Huter, {\i T. minimum} Ard.). Stock with elongated branches, the plant forming lax mats; stems usually 5-10 cm, erect. Rosette-leaves orbicular, the lamina abruptly contracted into the petiole; cauline leaves ovate, acute; all glaucous. Inflorescence rarely more than 3 cm in fruit. Petals 5 mm. Silicula 6 mm, narrowly obovate; apex truncate or with shallow notch; style 1-1·5 mm. Seeds 1-3 in each loculus. 2n = 14. •{\i  S.E. Alps, N. & C. Jugoslavia.} Au It Ju.
