\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\i  rotundifolium} (L.) Greuter & Burdet, {\i Willdenowia}{\b  15}: 71 (1985) ({\i T. rotundifolium} (L.) Gaudin, non Tineo, {\i T. lereschianum} Rouy & Fouc., {\i T. limosellifolium} Reuter; incl. subsp. {\i grignense} (F.K. Meyer) Greuter & Burdet): Basal leaves in a more or less distinct rosette; cauline leaves distant, auricled, the lower opposite; all more or less entire. Inflorescence remaining compact in fruit. Seeds 1-4 in each loculus. 2n = 14. {\i Throughout the range of the species}.
